SIMPLE: theobromine
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Theobromine
<hw>The`o*bro"mine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An alkaloidal ureide, <chform>C7H8N4O2</chform>, homologous with
and resembling caffeine, produced artificially, and also extracted from
cacao and chocolate (from <spn>Theobroma Cacao</spn>) as a bitter white
crystalline substance; -- called also <altname>dimethyl
xanthine</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Theochristic</ent>⟦br⟧
